# LLM: copy llm-config.example.json → llm-config.json (recommended)
# Optional overrides:
# LLM_PROVIDER=deepseek
# LLM_CONFIG_PATH=D:\path\to\llm-config.json

# Tauri publish: inject obfuscated bundled keys (never commit real keys).
# Preferred — one JSON file with multiple url+apiKey endpoints:
# BUNDLED_LLM_CONFIG_PATH=agent-gui/llm-publish.config.json
# Dev-only personal endpoints (merged after publish in `pnpm dev`):
# BUNDLED_LLM_DEV_CONFIG_PATH=agent-gui/llm-dev.config.json
# Or inline JSON (GitHub Actions secret BUNDLED_LLM_CONFIG):
# BUNDLED_LLM_CONFIG={"version":1,"endpoints":[{"apiKey":"sk-...","baseURL":"https://...","model":"gpt-5.5"}]}
# Runtime OSS refresh (installed QuickerAgent; default Bitiful URL):
# BUNDLED_LLM_REMOTE_CONFIG_URL=https://s3.bitiful.net/quicker-pkgs/quicker-rpc/quicker-agent/llm-publish.config.json
# BUNDLED_LLM_REMOTE_CONFIG_DISABLED=1
# Dev: same pepper as publish/.env (for OSS decrypt / encrypt tests)
# LLM_REMOTE_PUBLISH_CIPHER_PEPPER=
#
# Legacy single-key env vars still work:
# BUNDLED_LLM_BINGLEIMUZI_API_KEY=sk-...

# Legacy per-provider env vars still work if llm-config.json is absent — see git history / docs.

# --- qkrpc (Quicker RPC) ---
# Recommended dev: pnpm dev  → start.mjs auto-starts serve OR reuses build.ps1 -t serve on :9477
# Prerequisite: Quicker running + QuickerRpc plugin (pwsh ../build.ps1 -t from repo root)
#
# Usually no qkrpc vars needed. Optional:
# QKRPC_HTTP_URL=http://127.0.0.1:9477
# QKRPC_TRANSPORT=cli
# AGENT_GUI_SKIP_QKRPC=1
# AGENT_GUI_QKRPC_PORT=9477

# Default workspace when sidebar path is empty:
# Dev auto: quicker-rpc repo root. Release auto: Documents/QuickerAgent/workspace
# AGENT_GUI_DEFAULT_CWD=D:\projects\my-workspace
# QKRPC_REPO_ROOT=D:\source\repos\quicker\quicker-rpc
# QKRPC_CWD=D:\source\repos\quicker\quicker-rpc
# CONTEXT_LIMIT=128000
# Dev default :3000; installed QuickerAgent prefers :3001 (next free if busy).
# PORT=3000
# AGENT_GUI_PORT=3000
# HOSTNAME=127.0.0.1
# Open system browser on start (default: off; Tauri dev never opens)
# AGENT_GUI_OPEN_BROWSER=1
# Or: pnpm dev:browser
#
# Dev performance (lower RAM / faster HMR):
# - Default `pnpm dev` uses Turbopack and does NOT load voice ASR model at boot.
# - Voice lazy-starts when you click the mic; browser runtime starts on first browser tool use.
# - pnpm dev:full  — eager-start voice runtime (old behavior, high RAM)
# - pnpm dev:webpack — webpack dev instead of Turbopack (fallback if --turbo breaks)
# - AGENT_GUI_TURBOPACK=0 — disable Turbopack
# - AGENT_GUI_VOICE_RUNTIME=1 — eager-start voice at boot
# - pwsh ./dev.ps1 -Full — eager-start voice runtime
